# Item names + tooltip descriptions for the grove blooms and the shrine. A description renders as
# rich text on the item tooltip's TextSpans (Hytale's native <i>/<b>/<color is="#hex">/\n markup,
# parsed client-side per locale, exactly like vanilla items.*.description). Each highlight colour
# matches the bloom's own glow. No balance numbers in the flavor, so a tuning change never forces a
# localization edit. The _Plant clusters are the harvest source; the thrown blooms drop from them.
item.moonbloom.name = Moonbloom
item.moonbloom.description = Offer it at a blighted shrine to cleanse the grove, or hurl it to <color is="#7affa0">stun</color> a hunter where it bursts.\n\n<i>The grove's last clean light. It still remembers the song the Void tried to drown.</i>
item.moonbloom_plant.name = Moonbloom Cluster
item.moonbloom_plant.description = Harvest this glowing cluster to gather <color is="#7affa0">Moonbloom</color>, the light the shrines drink and the hunt fears.\n\n<i>Even choked by the blight, a little of the grove's old light keeps creeping back.</i>
item.gustbloom.name = Gustbloom
item.gustbloom.description = Bursts in a sharp <color is="#5a9cff">gust</color> that hurls a hunter back and buys you room to run.\n\n<i>It held its breath since the grove last breathed clean, and lets go all at once.</i>
item.gustbloom_plant.name = Gustbloom Cluster
item.gustbloom_plant.description = Harvest this windswept cluster to gather <color is="#5a9cff">Gustbloom</color>, the bloom that throws a hunter back.\n\n<i>It sways when there is no wind, breathing air the dead grove can no longer use.</i>
item.mirebloom.name = Mirebloom
item.mirebloom.description = Bursts into clinging spores that <color is="#7affa0">slow</color> whatever they touch. Drag the hunt down to a crawl.\n\n<i>It festered in the drowned roots where the blight pools thickest, and the mire clings to all that moves.</i>
item.mirebloom_plant.name = Mirebloom Cluster
item.mirebloom_plant.description = Harvest this sodden cluster to gather <color is="#7affa0">Mirebloom</color>, the bloom that drags the hunt to a crawl.\n\n<i>It thrives where the roots have drowned, growing fat on the standing rot.</i>
item.emberbloom.name = Emberbloom
item.emberbloom.description = Bursts into searing <color is="#ff8a3c">embers</color> that burn the blight and spare your fellow survivors.\n\n<i>Cracked from the Warden's own bark. Fire is the one shape the Void never learned to wear.</i>
item.emberbloom_plant.name = Emberbloom Cluster
item.emberbloom_plant.description = Harvest this smouldering cluster to gather <color is="#ff8a3c">Emberbloom</color>, the bloom that burns the blight away.\n\n<i>It takes root only where the Warden has walked, and it is always warm to the touch.</i>
item.shrine.name = Blighted Shrine
item.shrine.description = Offer <color is="#7affa0">Moonbloom</color> here to cleanse the blight. A relit shrine burns with green fire, and the hunt turns toward the light.\n\n<i>It once carried the grove's song. Now it waits cold for someone warm to wake it.</i>

