# Guide dialogue: the Grove Warden (id "nightmares_intro"). NODE TEXT renders on the
# Label's TextSpans, so Hytale's native inline markup - <color is="#hex">/<b>/<i> - is
# parsed CLIENT-side, per-locale (same mechanism as vanilla items.*.description). A
# translator keeps the markup in their own line. Option labels are TextButtons (no
# TextSpans), so they take no markup - colour-coded by their DialogueOptionStyle.
dialogue.nightmares_intro.npc = The Grove Warden
dialogue.nightmares_intro.greet.text = Warm. Breathing. Awake. You have no idea how rare that is down here. I have lived this same nightmare more nights than I have rings - the grove gone black, my own kin wearing my face, hunting me through the dark. I never make it out. But I have watched it enough times to know where it trips you. Sit a moment. Let me ruin the ending for you.
dialogue.nightmares_intro.greet.opt.0 = How does this nightmare go?
dialogue.nightmares_intro.greet.opt.1 = Enough talk. Send me in.
dialogue.nightmares_intro.greet.opt.2 = About the hunt I am already in...
dialogue.nightmares_intro.greet.opt.3 = Who has lasted the longest?
dialogue.nightmares_intro.lore.text = It always starts the same. The grove is dark and dead, and the only way to wake it is the shrines - feed them <color is="#7affa0">Moonbloom</color> light until they catch green fire. Here is the cruel part: lighting a shrine is loud, and the thing in the dark has wonderful ears. Funny how it always knows exactly where I am the moment I start to channel. Light every shrine and the <b>Heartwood Gate</b> opens - loudly, of course - and whoever stands nearest it is the first to be missed.
dialogue.nightmares_intro.lore.opt.0 = I have heard enough. Send me in.
dialogue.nightmares_intro.lore.opt.1 = So how do I actually survive it?
dialogue.nightmares_intro.tips.text = So you want to live. Bold of you. Keep your pockets full of blooms: a <color is="#7affa0">Moonbloom</color> to the face stuns the wretched things, a <color is="#5a9cff">Gustbloom</color> throws them back, a <color is="#7affa0">Mirebloom</color> drags them to a crawl, and an <color is="#ff8a3c">Emberbloom</color> burns them - them, mind, not your friends. If the roots take you, do not sulk down there; a warm hand can tear you free, so stay close enough to be that hand. And the way out only opens for those who stand on the platform <b>together</b> - wander off alone and the grove simply forgets to let you leave. Oh, and do hurry. Every breath you waste, the dark grows bolder, faster, <color is="#ff6b6b">hungrier</color>.
dialogue.nightmares_intro.tips.opt.0 = Now I am ready.
dialogue.nightmares_intro.tips.opt.1 = Go back.
dialogue.nightmares_intro.preset_pick.text = How deep into the nightmare do you want to go? Shallow, and it shambles - good for learning where the bodies fall. Deep, and it sprints, and the dark drinks your light faster than you can make it. Choose. I will be watching from somewhere safe.
dialogue.nightmares_intro.preset_pick.opt.0 = Amateur - let me learn the grove.
dialogue.nightmares_intro.preset_pick.opt.1 = Nightmare - the real hunt.
dialogue.nightmares_intro.preset_pick.opt.2 = Hardcore - one life, no second chances.
dialogue.nightmares_intro.preset_pick.opt.3 = Not yet. Step back.
dialogue.nightmares_intro.already_engaged.text = One nightmare at a time, warm one. You are already bound to a hunt. Slip out of that gathering first, and I will gladly throw you into the next.
dialogue.nightmares_intro.already_engaged.opt.0 = Understood.

