# Clash Host NPC + the clash_intro dialogue (the PvP entry).
npc.clashhost.name = The Duelmaster
npc.clashhost.hint = Press [{key}] to enter the arena
dialogue.clash_intro.npc = The Duelmaster
dialogue.clash_intro.greet.text = So. You would rather test your roots against another warm-blood than run from the dark. I respect that. The grove makes a fine arena when the only nightmare in it is each other. Stay sharp - I have buried better fighters than you, and I was not even trying.
dialogue.clash_intro.greet.opt.0 = How does the arena work?
dialogue.clash_intro.greet.opt.1 = I am ready to fight.
dialogue.clash_intro.greet.opt.2 = About the match I am already in...
dialogue.clash_intro.lore.text = Two teams, one grove, and shrooms sprouting from the soil: <color is="#5a9cff">knockback</color> to send a fool flying off the edge, <color is="#7affa0">stun</color> to leave them gawping while you swing. Grab them before the other side does - the ones who scavenge tend to be the ones who walk out. Last team standing takes it; if the clock runs dry, whoever landed the most blows wins, so do not just dance, hit something. In Domination, forget all that and simply hold the ground longer than they can.
dialogue.clash_intro.lore.opt.0 = Enough. Let me fight.
dialogue.clash_intro.lore.opt.1 = On second thought, go back.
dialogue.clash_intro.mode_pick.text = Name your contest, warm-blood. I will open the gate to whichever ground you fancy bleeding on.
dialogue.clash_intro.mode_pick.opt.0 = Clash 1v1 - just the two of us.
dialogue.clash_intro.mode_pick.opt.1 = Clash 2v2 - bring a friend to lose with.
dialogue.clash_intro.mode_pick.opt.2 = Domination - hold the ground.
dialogue.clash_intro.mode_pick.opt.3 = Not yet. Step back.
dialogue.clash_intro.already_engaged.text = One fight at a time, warm-blood. Finish the contest you are in, then come bleed for me again.
dialogue.clash_intro.already_engaged.opt.0 = Understood.
